<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="7" /><hi rend="italics">Larger advertisements in exact properties.</hi></p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="8" />Advertisements published until forbid, will be charged <measure n="50cents" type="currency">50 cents</measure> per square of <num value="8">eight</num> lines for the <num value="1" type="ordinal">first</num> insertion, and <measure n="25cents" type="currency">25 cents</measure> for each continuance</p> </div1> </front> <body> <milestone unit="column" n="1" /> 
<div1 type="notices" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<div2 type="official" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Official.</head> 
<div3 type="orders" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><orgName n="Treasury Department" type="department">Treasury Department</orgName>,</hi><lb /><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>,<lb /><hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 4" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>,</hi> <dateStruct value="1865-03-15" full="yes" authname="1865-03-15"><month reg="03" full="yes">March</month> <day reg="15" full="yes">15</day>, <year reg="1865" full="yes">1865</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<div4 type="entry" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="9" />Donations to the <name>Treasury</name>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="10" /> Patriotic citizens in all parts of the country having expressed a desire to make contributions of money and Government securities in aid of the <name>Treasury</name>; and ladies, animated by the noblest sentiments of attachment to the cause of their suffering country, having offered their plate and jewels, the <orgName n="Confederate States Congress" type="congress">Congress of the Confederate States</orgName> adopted on the <dateStruct value="--13" full="yes" authname="---13"><day reg="13" full="yes">13th instant</day></dateStruct> the following resolutions; </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="11" /> <num value="16">no. 16</num><unclear />--Joint resolution providing for Donations to the <name>Treasury</name> of the <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="12" /> Whereas, many Patriotic citizens have expressed their desire to contribute by Donations of money, <unclear /> gold and silvered plate, and public securities to the relief of the <name>Treasury</name>; Therefore. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="13" /> Resolved by the <orgName n="Confederate States Congress" type="congress">Congress of the Confederate States of <placeName reg="United States, North and Central America, " key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">America</placeName></orgName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="14" />That the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs> <unclear /> and he is hereby authorized to receive all <unclear /> donation, and to publish in the daily papers <unclear /> of the <name>Donations</name> received and the names of the <unclear /> </p> 
<list type="ordered"> 
<head /> 
<item n="1"> <hi rend="smallcaps">Section</hi> <num value="2">2</num>.That the said contributions shall consist of certificates of indebtedness, fully issued by the <unclear /> officers of the <rs>Government</rs>, and the <unclear /> holding the <unclear /> are willing to give a part, but liable to give the whole, it shall be lawful for <unclear /> the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs> to receive the proportion <unclear /> it not less than <num value="1">one</num> moiety, and to <unclear /> the other moiety in certificates of indebtedness, <unclear /> in payment of taxes.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="15" /></item> 
<item n="2"> <hi rend="smallcaps">Section</hi> <num value="3">3</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="16" />To render the said public securities so <unclear /> to the <name>Treasury</name>, the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs> to hereby authorized to redeem the <unclear /> before maturity, and of any moneys in the <name>Treasury</name> not otherwise appropriated.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="17" /></item> </list> 
<p> Approved <dateStruct value="1865-03-18" full="yes" authname="1865-03-18"><month reg="03" full="yes">March</month> <day reg="18" full="yes">18</day>, <year reg="1865" full="yes">1865</year></dateStruct>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="18" /> The attention of the public is called to these resolutions, and these desirous of making contributions <unclear /> and securities of certified claims against the <rs>Government</rs>, are respectfully informed that they will be received by the <rs>Treasurer</rs> at <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 4" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName> <unclear> </unclear> by the <rs type="role" reg="Assistant-Treasurer">Assistant Treasurers</rs> and Pay Depositaries to <unclear /> enumerated. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="19" /> Regulations in relation to plate and jewelry have <unclear /> adopted yet, and will form the subject of <unclear /> </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Trenholm,,G.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00005" reg="default:Trenholm,G.,A.,," authname="trenholm,g.,a."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Trenholm</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of Treasury</rs>.</signed> <term type="printrun"><unclear /></term> </closer> </div4> 
<div4 type="entry" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><unclear /> <rs type="role" reg="Assistant-Treasurer">Assistant Treasurers</rs> and Pay Depositaries in the <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, Viz:</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="20" /> Treasurer <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Virginia</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="21" /> <rs type="role" reg="Assistant-Treasurer">Assistant Treasurer</rs> <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Charleston, Charleston, South Carolina" key="tgn,7013582" authname="tgn,7013582">Charleston, South Carolina</placeName>. </p> 
<p> <rs type="role" reg="Assistant-Treasurer">Assistant Treasurer</rs> <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Mobile, Mobile, Alabama" key="tgn,7017444" authname="tgn,7017444">Mobile, Alabama</placeName>. </p> 
<p> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Montgomery, Montgomery, Alabama" key="tgn,7013928" authname="tgn,7013928">Montgomery, Alabama</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="22" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Augusta, Richmond, Georgia" key="tgn,7017498" authname="tgn,7017498">Augusta, Georgia</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="23" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Atlanta, Fulton, Georgia" key="tgn,7013331" authname="tgn,7013331">Atlanta, Georgia</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="24" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Macon, Bibb, Georgia" key="tgn,7013980" authname="tgn,7013980">Macon, Georgia</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="25" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Columbus, Muscogee, Georgia" key="tgn,7013643" authname="tgn,7013643">Columbus, Georgia</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="26" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Columbia, Richland, South Carolina" key="tgn,7013641" authname="tgn,7013641">Columbia, South Carolina</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="27" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Raleigh, Wake, North Carolina" key="tgn,7013949" authname="tgn,7013949">Raleigh, North Carolina</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="28" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Greensboro, Guilford, North Carolina" key="tgn,7014135" authname="tgn,7014135">Greensboro', North Carolina</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="29" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Tallahassee, Leon, Florida" key="tgn,7013938" authname="tgn,7013938">Tallahassee, Florida</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="30" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Lynchburg, Lynchburg, Virginia" key="tgn,7013981" authname="tgn,7013981">Lynchburg, Virginia</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="31" /> Pay Depositary <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName>, <placeName reg="Columbus, Lowndes, Mississippi" key="tgn,2056204" authname="tgn,2056204">Columbus, Mississippi</placeName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="32" /> <term type="printrun">mh 26</term> </p> </div4> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Treasury Notice in relation to Receipt of <num value="0.06">Six Per Cent.</num> Certificates of Indebtedness for taxes imposed by act of Congress, Approved <dateStruct value="1865-03-11" full="yes" authname="1865-03-11"><month reg="03" full="yes">March</month> <day reg="11" full="yes">11</day>, <year reg="1865" full="yes">1865</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<div4 type="entry" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="33" /> --Notice is hereby given that according to the provisions of the <orgName type="regiment" key="3Section">third section</orgName> of act of Congress of <dateStruct value="1865-03-11" full="yes" authname="1865-03-11"><month reg="03" full="yes">March</month> <day reg="11" full="yes">11</day>, <year reg="1865" full="yes">1865</year></dateStruct>, a copy of which is <unclear /> attached <num value="1">one</num> moiety of the taxes levied by <unclear /> act (excepting the tax for the increased pay of soldiers may be paid in <num value="0.06">six per cent.</num> Certificates of Indebtedness issued under <orgName type="regiment" key="14Section">fourteenth section</orgName> of <unclear /> of <dateStruct value="1865-02-17" full="yes" authname="1865-02-17"><day reg="17" full="yes">17th</day> <month reg="02" full="yes">February</month>, <year reg="1865" full="yes">1865</year></dateStruct>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Trenholm,,G.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00006" reg="default:Trenholm,G.,A.,," authname="trenholm,g.,a."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Trenholm</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of Treasury</rs>.</signed> </closer> </div4> 
<div4 type="entry" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="34" /> Section <num value="3">3</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="35" />That the taxes on property for the <unclear /> <num value="1865">eighteen hundred and sixty- five</num> imposed by the act, shall be assessed as on the day of the <unclear /> of this act, and be due and collected on the <dateStruct value="-06-1" full="yes" authname="--06-01"><day reg="1" full="yes">first</day> day of <month reg="06" full="yes">June</month></dateStruct> next, or as soon thereafter as pacification.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="36" />The additional taxes on profits for the year <dateStruct value="1865" full="yes" authname="1865"><year reg="1865" full="yes">eighteen hundred and sixty-five</year></dateStruct> shall be assessed and collected according to provisions of existing <unclear /> in regard to the assessment and collection of taxes on <unclear /> and all the taxes imposed by this act as well as the taxes on incomes and profits and the specific taxes and taxes on sales, shall be payable in <orgName n="Confederate Treasury notes" type="org">Confederate Treasury notes</orgName> of the new issue, of in the <name>Certificates</name> of Indebtedness authorized by an <unclear />entitled "an act to reduce the currency and to authorize a new issue of notes and bonds," approved <dateStruct value="1864-02-17" full="yes" authname="1864-02-17"><month reg="02" full="yes">February</month> <day reg="17" full="yes">17th</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>, at par, without any allowance for interest; Provided, That at least <num value="1">one</num> <unclear> </unclear> of said taxes shall be paid in Treasury notes as aforesaid; and provided further, That the tax for the increased pay of soldiers shall be paid in <orgName n="Confederate Treasury notes" type="org">Confederate Treasury notes</orgName> of the new issue only; and it is nearby enacted that the <name>Certificates</name> of Indebtedness authorized by the said act of <dateStruct value="1864-02-17" full="yes" authname="1864-02-17"><month reg="02" full="yes">February</month> <day reg="17" full="yes">17</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>, may be issued for debts contracted prior to the passage of said act, and the agent of the <name>Treasury</name> for the <orgName n="Department of Trans-Mississippi" type="department">Trans-Mississippi Department</orgName> be, and he is hereby authorized to issue under regulations to be presented by the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs> the <name>Certificates</name> of Indebtedness provided for in said act of <dateStruct value="1864-02-17" full="yes" authname="1864-02-17"><month reg="02" full="yes">February</month> <day reg="17" full="yes">17</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>, for debts contracted prior or subsequent to the passage of said act in the <orgName n="Department of Trans-Mississippi" type="department">Trans-Mississippi Department</orgName>; and that all the certificates above mentioned shall be received in payment <unclear /> taxes in like manner and to the same extent as the certificates originally authorized by the said act of <dateStruct value="1864-02-17" full="yes" authname="1864-02-17"><day reg="17" full="yes">17th</day> of <month reg="02" full="yes">February</month>, <year full="yes">1864</year>,</dateStruct> subject to the proviso above mentioned. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="37" /> <term type="printrun">mar 16--eod1m.</term> </p> </div4> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="3" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><orgName n="Treasury Department" type="department">Treasury Department</orgName>,</hi><lb /><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>,<lb /><hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 4" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>,</hi> <dateStruct value="1865-03-15" full="yes" authname="1865-03-15"><month reg="03" full="yes">March</month> <day reg="15" full="yes">15</day>, <year reg="1865" full="yes">1865</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="38" />Notice to Holders of Certificates of <num value="0.04">Four Per Cent.</num> Bonds, issued by the <name>Depositary</name> at <placeName key="tgn,2115154" n="1.000 60" reg="wytheville, wythe, virginia" authname="tgn,2115154">Wytheville</placeName>, Va.--The Depositary at <placeName key="tgn,2115154" n="1.000 60" reg="wytheville, wythe, virginia" authname="tgn,2115154">Wytheville</placeName> having resigned, and the office <unclear> </unclear> notice is hereby given to holders of certificates for <num value="0.04">four per cent.</num> Bonds, under Act of <dateStruct value="1864-02-17" full="yes" authname="1864-02-17"><day reg="17" full="yes">17th</day> <month reg="02" full="yes">February</month>, <year full="yes">1864</year>,</dateStruct> issued at that office, that the same will be satisfied with Bonds upon application to the <unclear /> of the <name>Treasury</name> at <placeName key="tgn,7013964" n="1.000 4" reg="richmond, richmond, virginia" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>. </p> <closer> <signed>[Signed] <persName n="Trenholm,,G.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00007" reg="default:Trenholm,G.,A.,," authname="trenholm,g.,a."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Trenholm</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Treasury,Secretary,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00008" reg="mostcommon:Treasury,nomatch:0" authname="treasury"><roleName n="Secretary" full="yes">Secretary</roleName> <surname full="yes">Treasury</surname></persName>.</signed> <term type="printrun">mh 17--<unclear />w2w</term> </closer> </div3> </div2> 
